EMPIRICAL EVIDENCE:
The study found that schema changes often lead to code modifications- and vice versa. By keeping schema and code in sync- 
1) projects can foster better communication and collaboration between database administrators and developers; 

2) projects can improve their documentation and make it easier for new developers to understand the application's structure and behavior; 

3) projects can raise awareness of the importance of considering both aspects when making design decisions and adopting more sustainable software development practices; 

4) projects can reduce the effort required for maintenance and evolution

5) projects can reduce the likelihood of inconsistencies- conflicts- and bugs
